quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,79,"They said, "
  11,80,"He said, "
  11,81,"They [the angels] said, ",footnotes:1:i.e., sometime before dawn.
  12,40,"You worship not besides Him except [mere] names you have named them,{1} you and your fathers, for which Allāh has sent down no evidence. Legislation is not but for Allāh. He has commanded that you worship not except Him. That is the correct religion, but most of the people do not know.",footnotes:1:The false objects of worship which you have called "gods."
  12,41,"O two companions of prison, as for one of you, he will give drink to his master of wine; but as for the other, he will be crucified, and the birds will eat from his head. The matter has been decreed about which you both inquire."
  12,42,"And he said to the one whom he knew would go free, "
  13,7,"And those who disbelieved say, "
  13,8,"Allāh knows what every female carries{1} and what the wombs lose [prematurely] or exceed.{2} And everything with Him is by due measure.",footnotes:1:[With absolute knowledge inclusive of every aspect of the fetus' existence.],footnotes:2:[Beyond their normal period of pregnancy and/or the number of fetuses therein.]
  13,9,"[He is] Knower of the unseen and the witnessed, the Grand, the Exalted."
